<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7906] CqlConfigHelper disables the connection pool for remote hosts while the remote hosts can be used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7906</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7774&quot; title=&quot;CqlRecordReader creates wrong cluster if the first replica of a split is down&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-7774&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-7774&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The new load balancing policy does not allow using non-replica hosts, but it distinguishes local replica and remote replica, and returns them in appropriate order. However, CqlConfigHelper disables remote hosts completely.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
